                            <comment id="17154443" author="paulk" created="Thu, 9 Jul 2020 11:25:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We are aware of incomplete work in our JSR 308/JEP 104 implementation, see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-8225&quot; title=&quot;Groovy support for JSR 308/JEP 104 (Annotations in more places)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;GROOVY-8225&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;GROOVY-8225&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; but thanks for the reminder. We&apos;ll have to find time to increase its priority.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17345687" author="daniel_sun" created="Sun, 16 May 2021 11:42:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The proposed PR has been merged. Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17554454" author="JIRAUSER291023" created="Wed, 15 Jun 2022 08:16:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hello, as this is a bug in 3.0.4 why the correction was made in 4.0.0 ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there a way to backport this correction to groovy 3.x version please ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17554828" author="paulk" created="Thu, 16 Jun 2022 00:02:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;To support type annotations involved numerous changes to the public API including things as fundamental as ClassNode and how we handled representing primitive types throughout the codebase, e.g. one of the related commits:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/a258e2fd&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/groovy/commit/a258e2fd&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;It wouldn&apos;t be safe to backport all of that in a 3.0.x point release.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What is your use case? There might be a small number of cases which could be made to work with the previous design.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17556243" author="JIRAUSER291023" created="Mon, 20 Jun 2022 07:43:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I wanted to use javax.validation on container like List&amp;lt;@NotBlank String&amp;gt; to ensure that the items in the list are not blank.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Moreover i have a some groovy/grails legacy code and grails seems to not be compatible with groovy 4.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then i think here to only report the type parameter annotation from source to bytecode. I&apos;m aware that the &apos;only&apos; may need a lot of work...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
